The Kaduna State Pilgrims Board has launched a curriculum for hajj pilgrims guides titled ‘Jagoran Mahajjata’ for intending pilgrims in the state. Speaking at the launching of the Renewed Curriculum Development on Hajj Pilgrims Guide titled Jagoran Mahajjata to stakeholders in the state, it said the compilation will help address the challenges pilgrims face. He said the new guide will further educate the intending pilgrims on their expectations in the holy land. On the trainers teaching intending pilgrims, Dr Alrigasiyu said they would be expected to follow the guide during the enlightenment exercise for intending pilgrims. 